
What is Amazon EMR?

Amazon Elastic MapReduce (EMR) is a big data processing service in AWS.

It lets you process and analyze huge volumes of data (terabytes–petabytes) quickly and cost-effectively.

It lets you create Hadoop clusters (Big data) to analyze and process vast amount of data 

Uses open-source frameworks like:

Apache Hadoop

Apache Spark

Presto

Hive

HBase

Flink




---

Key Features

Managed cluster of EC2 instances → AWS sets up Hadoop/Spark clusters for you.

Can process data stored in S3, DynamoDB, HDFS, or local disks.